When reaching out to your new manager to inform them that today is your last day in your current team and inquire if there are any pending tasks or responsibilities that you need to complete, it's important to be professional, concise, and polite. Here's a suggested approach for your message:

Subject: Last Day in Current Team - Pending Tasks?

Dear [Manager's Name],

I hope this email finds you well. I wanted to inform you that today is my last day with [current team/department]. I am excited about joining your team and look forward to contributing to its success.

Before transitioning, I wanted to reach out and ask if there are any pending tasks or responsibilities that I need to complete before leaving my current role. I want to ensure a smooth handover and address any outstanding work, if necessary. Please let me know if there's anything specific you'd like me to focus on today.

I will do my best to wrap up any loose ends and ensure a seamless transition for the team. If you have any instructions or suggestions for a smooth handover process, I would greatly appreciate your guidance.

Thank you for your understanding and support during this transition period. I'm excited about the new challenges and opportunities that lie ahead.

Best regards,
[Your Name]

Remember to adapt this template to your own style and any specific circumstances. It's essential to maintain professionalism and a positive tone throughout your communication.
